-- South African Coal Export Prices Fall to Lowest in 17 Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-04-23T13:21:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/south-african-coal-export-prices-fall-to-lowest-in-17-months.html
Coal export prices at  South
Africa ’s Richards Bay, the continent’s biggest terminal for
shipping the fuel, fell to the lowest level in seventeen months.  Prices fell $2.19, or 2.1 percent, to $100.38 a metric ton
in the week ended April 20, according to IHS McCloskey data on
Bloomberg. That’s the lowest level since Nov. 5, 2010.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  